## Implementation Plan

### Problem
After upgrading the CLI, the setup command (called by upgrade) outputs:
1. 'Agent skills: Updated <path>' — on every upgrade, even though nothing changed for the user
2. 'Get started:' welcome message — irrelevant for existing users upgrading
3. 'Setup complete!' — redundant since the upgrade command prints its own success message

### Changes

#### 1. handleAgentSkills() — suppress on update (setup.ts:224-232)
Same pattern as completions fix in PR #326. installAgentSkills() already returns
`created: boolean`. Changed from printing 'Installed to' / 'Updated' to only
printing when `created === true`.

#### 2. handleInstall() — track if binary already existed (setup.ts:65-93)
Added `existsSync(targetPath)` check before calling `installBinary()`.
Returns new `created: boolean` field in result object. Uses getBinaryFilename()
+ join() to construct the expected install path before installation.

#### 3. func() — welcome only on fresh install (setup.ts:457-489)
Track `freshInstall` from handleInstall's `created` field. Welcome message
(printWelcomeMessage) only shown when `freshInstall === true`.
Removed the 'Setup complete!' fallback entirely — it served no purpose when
called from upgrade (which prints its own success message).

### Behavior Table
| Scenario | Output |
|----------|--------|
| Fresh install (--install, no binary) | Binary path + welcome + getting started |
| Curl upgrade (--install, binary exists) | Binary path only |
| npm/pnpm upgrade (no --install) | Silent |
| Manual re-run | Silent |
| Any + --quiet | Silent |

### Tests Added/Updated
- 'produces no welcome or completion output without --install' (was 'outputs Setup complete!')
- '--install suppresses welcome when binary already exists (upgrade)' (new)
- 'suppresses agent skills message on subsequent runs (upgrade scenario)' (new)
- 'does not break setup on network failure' — updated to not expect 'Setup complete!'
- 'bestEffort catches errors...' — updated to check for Warning instead of 'Setup complete!'
